Question: Develop an argument for or against the following statement: television violence is appropriate for audiences of all ages
Answer:
I don't think television violence is appropriate for every audiences because young people and especially kids find it hard sometimes to make a difference between reality and fiction, between life and what they see on television. Witnessing violence on television might lead them to be more shocked than adults. Or, even worse, they might consider this violence as normal and don't understand what is wrong with it.